setInvFootPrint(25.10)                                  setInvFootPrint(25.10)

Name
       setInvFootPrint - Specifies the inverter cell footprints

Syntax
       setInvFootPrint

       [-help]

       [-library <libName>]

       <invCellOrFootprintNames>

       Specifies the inverter cell footprints. The footprint names are usually
       assigned during design import. The Innovus software uses these inverter
       footprint  names  during timing optimization and top-level inverter in-
       sertion in a partition design.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each setInvFootPrint parameter. For  a  detailed  de-
              scription  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man
              command:

              man setInvFootPrint

       <invCellOrFootprintNames>
              Specifies the inverter cell footprint  names  or  inverter  cell
              names. When you specify an inverter cell name, the Innovus soft-
              ware automatically finds the cell footprint name.

       -library <libName>
              Specifies  the  library name from where the cells will be picked
              up.

Related Information
              * checkFootPrint

              * loadFootPrint

              * setBufFootPrint

              * setDelayFootPrint

              * The following topic in the Innovus User Guide

                * Using Cell Footprints in Timing Optimization

